  "title" : "Why doesn&#39;t the MOVE_CURSOR show up on OSX Mountain Lion?",
  "body" : "<p>I'm working on project and want to see what each of the cursors provided by Swing look like.</p>\n\n<pre><code>public class Test {\n    public static void main(String args[]){\n        JFrame frame = new JFrame();\n\n        frame.setCursor(new Cursor(Cursor.MOVE_CURSOR));\n        frame.setSize(400, 400);\n\n        frame.setVisible(true);\n    }\n\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>However, when I use the crosshair cursor it works.</p>\n\n<pre><code>frame.setCursor(new Cursor(Cursor.CROSSHAIR_CURSOR));\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>When I mouseover the frame, it only shows the default cursor. It doesn't change to the move cursor. Are cursor implementations platform dependent?</p>\n"
}